257
00:21:04,156 --> 00:21:08,344
<i>Professor of genetics, Charles Francis Xavier.
[applause]</i>

258
00:21:10,982 --> 00:21:13,150
So, how does it feel to be a professor?

259
00:21:13,151 --> 00:21:14,228
Well ah, don't call me that.

260
00:21:14,228 --> 00:21:17,661
You don't get to be called a
Professor until you actually have a teaching position.

261
00:21:16,814 --> 00:21:19,919
- I know, but it suits you.
- No, don't say that, do say "Let's go have a drink".

262
00:21:20,046 --> 00:21:21,843
- Let's go have a drink.
- Wonderful!

263
00:21:33,994 --> 00:21:37,639
VILLA GESELL, ARGENTINA

264
00:21:49,748 --> 00:21:52,728
- Good afternoon, my friends!
- Good afternoon!

265
00:21:52,837 --> 00:21:54,097
- Hot, is not it?
- Yes...

266
00:21:54,210 --> 00:21:55,706
One beer, please.

267
00:22:03,066 --> 00:22:05,536
<Sebastian Shaw in middle of the picture>

268
00:22:19,590 --> 00:22:21,774
- German beer.
- Of course.

269
00:22:22,041 --> 00:22:25,524
Yes, it's Bitburger. You like it?

270
00:22:32,061 --> 00:22:33,450
The best.

271
00:22:38,772 --> 00:22:41,307
What brings you to Argentina?

272
00:22:43,046 --> 00:22:46,524
The climate, I'm a pig farmer.

273
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:53,632
I am a tailor, Have been my whole life.

274
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:56,427
My father made the finest suits in Düsseldorf.

275
00:22:57,361 --> 00:22:59,751
My Parents were from, Düsseldorf.

276
00:23:01,731 --> 00:23:04,661
- What was their name?
- They didn't have a name.

277
00:23:06,689 --> 00:23:08,624
It was taken away from them...

278
00:23:09,027 --> 00:23:10,338
...by pig farmers...

279
00:23:11,664 --> 00:23:13,165
...and tailors.

280
00:23:42,205 --> 00:23:43,755
"Blood and Honor".

281
00:23:43,927 --> 00:23:45,860
Which would you care to shed first?

282
00:23:45,949 --> 00:23:49,037
- We carried out the orders.
- Blood then.

283
00:23:49,826 --> 00:23:51,011
[Screaming]

284
00:23:51,707 --> 00:23:54,217
- Do not move, asshole!
- Go ahead, shoot!

285
00:24:04,513 --> 00:24:05,602
[trick]
[bang : gunshot]

286
00:24:06,351 --> 00:24:07,098
[Scream]  / [swish] / [Gasping] / [swoosh]

287
00:24:08,785 --> 00:24:09,886
[groan]

288
00:24:15,060 --> 00:24:17,167
Who, what are you?

289
00:24:20,085 --> 00:24:22,515
Let's just say I'm Frankenstein's monster.

290
00:24:34,918 --> 00:24:36,823
I'm looking for my creator.

291
00:24:39,830 --> 00:24:40,572
[bang : gunshot]

292
00:24:41,834 --> 00:24:45,799
Drink, drink, drink!
[clapping]

293
00:24:47,226 --> 00:24:48,170
[laughs]

294
00:24:48,171 --> 00:24:49,171
Woowwwww.....

295
00:24:52,206 --> 00:24:53,446
yeahhhhhhhhhhhh

296
00:24:59,432 --> 00:25:01,404
Oh, I'm so proud of  you.

297
00:25:06,247 --> 00:25:09,945
- Congratulations, Professor!
- Thank you very much, it's much harder than it looks, actually..

298
00:25:10,058 --> 00:25:12,538
- No, on your presentation.
- You knew my presentation?

299
00:25:12,645 --> 00:25:13,986
How nice of you, thank you very much.

300
00:25:14,110 --> 00:25:15,939
- Moira MacTaggert.
- Charles Xavier.

301
00:25:16,046 --> 00:25:17,188
Do you have a minute?

302
00:25:17,293 --> 00:25:21,551
For a pretty little beam with a
mutated MCR-1 gene, I have five.

303
00:25:21,981 --> 00:25:26,279
I say, MCR-1, you would say,
golden hair.

304
00:25:26,428 --> 00:25:30,035
It's a mutation, it's a very groovy mutation.

305
00:25:30,171 --> 00:25:34,710
Mutation you know, took us from single
cell organisms,

306
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:36,632
to the dominate form...

307
00:25:36,738 --> 00:25:40,895
You know what, this routine may go over great
with the co-eds, but I'm here on business.

308
00:25:41,220 --> 00:25:43,651
- What?
- I really need your help.

309
00:25:44,389 --> 00:25:45,716
All right.

310
00:25:45,825 --> 00:25:49,162
The kind that of mutations that you were
talking about in your thesis

311
00:25:49,319 --> 00:25:51,755
I need to know if they may already have happened.

312
00:25:53,020 --> 00:25:54,966
In people alive today.

313
00:26:06,590 --> 00:26:07,852
Professor?

314
00:26:09,990 --> 00:26:11,473
I think that we should just talk when you're sober.

315
00:26:11,580 --> 00:26:12,970
Do  you have any time tomorrow?

316
00:26:14,533 --> 00:26:18,460
Something tells me, you already know
the answer to your question.

317
00:26:20,488 --> 00:26:21,861
This is very important to me.

318
00:26:21,957 --> 00:26:24,560
And if I can help you, I will do my utmost.

319
00:26:25,434 --> 00:26:26,308
Thank you.

320
00:26:26,447 --> 00:26:29,146
MIAMI, FLORIDA

321
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:33,277
- Still drinking champagne, Bob?
- I will pass.

322
00:26:34,041 --> 00:26:37,004
Okay, well so much for the pleasantries.

323
00:26:37,550 --> 00:26:40,987
I was wondering, who you told
about our little arrangement?

324
00:26:41,391 --> 00:26:42,668
No one.

325
00:26:45,196 --> 00:26:47,385
- He's telling the truth.
- Good.

326
00:26:47,488 --> 00:26:51,545
Well I guess we're done here.
Let's wrap things up, shall we?

327
00:26:55,571 --> 00:26:58,251
Well I knew better than to trust you.

328
00:26:59,033 --> 00:27:02,481
Now you let me walk out of here
with my money.

329
00:27:02,482 --> 00:27:06,530
Or I will pull this pin and we all die.

330
00:27:07,425 --> 00:27:10,399
Go ahead, pull it.

331
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,060
I'll do it, I swear to god.

332
00:27:21,858 --> 00:27:23,259
No you won't.

333
00:27:28,393 --> 00:27:29,688
But I will.

334
00:27:30,302 --> 00:27:32,424
[clank]

335
00:27:34,211 --> 00:27:35,619
[boom]

336
00:27:35,654 --> 00:27:38,319
[humming]

337
00:27:43,138 --> 00:27:44,367
You're one of them?

338
00:27:44,475 --> 00:27:48,298
Very astute of you, Colonel Hendry.
You want to guess what I can do?

339
00:27:48,414 --> 00:27:51,308
I've got the power to absorb energy.
It keeps me young.

340
00:27:51,464 --> 00:27:52,936
That's the boring part.

341
00:27:53,096 --> 00:27:56,706
The fun stuff is what I can do with it
once I got it.

342
00:28:01,918 --> 00:28:03,539
CIA Headquarters, Langley, Virginia

343
00:28:03,667 --> 00:28:06,754
The advent of the nuclear age,
may have accelerated the mutation process.

344
00:28:06,910 --> 00:28:11,729
Individual's with extraordinary abilities may
already be among us.

345
00:28:12,498 --> 00:28:13,492
Thank you very much.

346
00:28:13,603 --> 00:28:16,583
MacTaggert, you really think that some crackpot scientist,

347
00:28:16,707 --> 00:28:20,298
is going to make me believe in sparkly dames
and vanishing men?

348
00:28:20,424 --> 00:28:23,167
You just brought yourself a one way ticket
back to the typing pool.

349
00:28:23,414 --> 00:28:24,889
This meeting is over.

350
00:28:25,020 --> 00:28:27,549
Uh, please sit down agent, MacTaggert.

351
00:28:28,423 --> 00:28:30,372
I didn't really expect you to believe me.

352
00:28:30,527 --> 00:28:32,431
Given that all you could think about during my presentation,

353
00:28:32,556 --> 00:28:35,130
was what sort of pie they were serving in the commissary.

354
00:28:36,205 --> 00:28:38,060
It's apple pecan.

355
00:28:38,356 --> 00:28:40,683
I haven't been entirely honest with you, and I'm sorry.

356
00:28:40,790 --> 00:28:44,870
You see, one of the many spectacular things my
mutation allows me to do.

357
00:28:44,987 --> 00:28:47,799
Is that I can your  mind.

358
00:28:47,911 --> 00:28:49,500
I've seen this before in a magic show.

359
00:28:49,652 --> 00:28:53,426
Are you going to ask us to think of a number
between one and ten now?

360
00:28:53,556 --> 00:28:55,206
No, agent Stryker.

361
00:28:55,329 --> 00:28:58,700
Although I could ask  you about your son William who
you were thinking about,

362
00:28:58,808 --> 00:29:00,057
which is very nice

363
00:29:00,187 --> 00:29:02,245
But I think I'd rather ask you
about the Jupiter...

364
00:29:02,381 --> 00:29:04,985
...missiles America are currently placing in Turkey.

365
00:29:06,827 --> 00:29:09,546
He's a goddamn spy!
You brought a goddamn spy!

366
00:29:09,719 --> 00:29:11,243
I did not, I would never bring one here!

367
00:29:11,541 --> 00:29:12,199
[hissing]

368
00:29:28,170 --> 00:29:28,584
[hissing]

369
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:32,383
How's that for a magic trick?

370
00:29:35,515 --> 00:29:37,843
Best I've ever seen.

371
00:29:38,450 --> 00:29:39,915
I want them out of here.

372
00:29:40,072 --> 00:29:43,221
And lock down until I can figure out
what to do.

373
00:29:44,173 --> 00:29:48,467
My facility is off site. I'll take them.

374
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:50,905
I can't believe this.

375
00:29:51,011 --> 00:29:53,463
You'd think the director of the CIA
would have a little more composure.

376
00:29:53,583 --> 00:29:54,961
We should be going after Shaw right now, but...

377
00:29:55,072 --> 00:29:57,078
...instead he's up there worrying about the wrong mutants.

378
00:29:57,327 --> 00:29:58,409
What are we doing to do, Lavene?

379
00:29:59,038 --> 00:30:02,014
Lavene?
Lavene, what's wrong with you?

380
00:30:04,393 --> 00:30:08,236
<i>Absolutely nothing, I've just frozen him for the
moment because I'd like to talk to you.</i>

381
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:09,522
<i>It's good, isn't it?</i>

382
00:30:09,523 --> 00:30:12,426
<i>I'm as interested in this Sebastian Shaw as you are,</i>

383
00:30:12,427 --> 00:30:15,539
<i>..and if you still want my help, meet me on
the third floor of the parking garage.</i>

384
00:30:16,605 --> 00:30:19,315
I've always known that there were people like
you out there.

385
00:30:19,442 --> 00:30:22,934
I've been the laughing stock of this agency
for years but I knew it.

386
00:30:23,027 --> 00:30:24,105
- You're going to love my facility.

387
00:30:24,217 --> 00:30:25,993
- That's going to have to wait.
- Why?

388
00:30:26,136 --> 00:30:28,018
Agent MacTaggert has to lead us to Sebastian Shaw,

389
00:30:28,144 --> 00:30:30,436
and if we don't move now apparently
we're going to lose him.

390
00:30:30,608 --> 00:30:31,312
What?

391
00:30:31,425 --> 00:30:34,586
Not only can he read minds,
he can communicate with them as well.

392
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:36,494
Moria and I have just had a lovely conversation.

393
00:30:36,600 --> 00:30:38,521
- Yes, we did.
- That is incredible!

394
00:30:39,833 --> 00:30:43,078
But I cannot take you anywhere else,
without permission from upstairs.

395
00:30:43,170 --> 00:30:45,332
- Would you like to see one more magic trick?
- Okay.

396
00:30:45,432 --> 00:30:47,023
- Get in the car.
- Good idea.

397
00:30:52,208 --> 00:30:58,440
[rippling]

398
00:31:01,383 --> 00:31:01,893
[dipping water sounds]

399
00:31:08,475 --> 00:31:09,768
Herr Doctor...

400
00:31:13,669 --> 00:31:16,055
the same old Erik Lensherr.

401
00:31:16,449 --> 00:31:17,928
He's here to kill you.

402
00:31:24,577 --> 00:31:26,963
What kind of greeting is that?

403
00:31:29,708 --> 00:31:31,890
After so many years?

404
00:31:41,478 --> 00:31:42,987
Emma...

405
00:31:43,940 --> 00:31:45,988
We don't harm our own kind.

406
00:31:48,512 --> 00:31:50,116
Ah, now it's a party.

407
00:31:51,165 --> 00:31:55,784
This is the US Coast guard.
Do not attempt to move your vessel.

408
00:31:55,919 --> 00:31:57,714
Stay where you are.

409
00:32:03,864 --> 00:32:05,204
They have a telepath.

410
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:10,500
I've lost, Shaw!

411
00:32:10,818 --> 00:32:12,536
I've lost, I've lost, Shaw.

412
00:32:12,537 --> 00:32:15,439
There's, there's something blocking me.
This has never happened to me before.

413
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:17,245
I think there's someone like
me on that ship.

414
00:32:17,401 --> 00:32:20,177
- Like you?
- I'm sorry, a telepath.

415
00:32:20,349 --> 00:32:22,804
This is incredible, I can actually feel
her inside my mind.

416
00:32:22,809 --> 00:32:24,736
I'm very sorry, but I don't think I'm
going to be much help to you tonight.

417
00:32:24,842 --> 00:32:25,840
You're on your own.

418
00:32:25,841 --> 00:32:28,261
[spalshings]

419
00:32:34,055 --> 00:32:36,464
[swirl]

420
00:32:39,982 --> 00:32:41,483
- Oh my god.
- Jesus.

421
00:32:45,001 --> 00:32:45,983
Get inside.

422
00:32:49,482 --> 00:32:52,065
[chink of anchor chains]

423
00:32:52,210 --> 00:32:53,534
Stop, stop, stop!

424
00:32:54,325 --> 00:32:57,261
Charles! You okay?

425
00:32:57,369 --> 00:32:58,877
There's someone else out there.

426
00:33:02,808 --> 00:33:04,097
There!

427
00:33:06,997 --> 00:33:08,186
Time to go.

428
00:34:03,268 --> 00:34:04,657
Let go!

429
00:34:06,548 --> 00:34:08,014
Better let it go!

430
00:34:08,119 --> 00:34:09,917
You've got help him...there's
someone in the water, help him!

431
00:34:10,007 --> 00:34:13,458
Let it go!
You have to let it go!

432
00:34:33,235 --> 00:34:36,623
<i>You can't, you'll drown.
You have to let go.</i>

433
00:34:36,714 --> 00:34:39,444
<i>I know what this means to you
but you're going to die.</i>

434
00:34:39,725 --> 00:34:43,765
<i>Please, Erik, calm your mind.</i>

435
00:34:55,589 --> 00:34:57,118
Get off of me, get off!

436
00:34:57,228 --> 00:34:58,609
Calm down,
Oh just breath.

437
00:34:58,609 --> 00:34:59,220
We're here!

438
00:34:59,575 --> 00:35:01,567
- Who are you?
-  My name is Charles Xavier.

439
00:35:01,689 --> 00:35:03,565
You were in my head.

440
00:35:03,842 --> 00:35:05,184
How did you do that?

441
00:35:05,292 --> 00:35:06,604
You have your tricks, I have mine.

442
00:35:06,713 --> 00:35:09,132
I'm like you, just calm your mind.

443
00:35:11,493 --> 00:35:15,348
- I thought I was alone.
- You're not alone.

444
00:35:16,862 --> 00:35:20,165
Erik, you're not alone.

445
00:35:22,450 --> 00:35:26,094
Secret CIA base.

446
00:35:40,103 --> 00:35:42,114
Welcome to my facility.

447
00:35:42,993 --> 00:35:44,518
My mission has been to investigate the

448
00:35:44,632 --> 00:35:48,109
application of paranormal powers
for military defense.

449
00:35:48,215 --> 00:35:49,509
Or offense.

450
00:35:49,806 --> 00:35:52,914
This guy, Shaw, Schmidt, whatever
you want to call him.

451
00:35:53,050 --> 00:35:54,725
He's working with the Russians.

452
00:35:54,850 --> 00:35:56,404
We might need your help to stop them.

453
00:35:56,518 --> 00:35:57,407
Marvelous.

454
00:35:57,532 --> 00:36:00,227
So we're to be the CIA's new
mutant division, yes?

455
00:36:01,405 --> 00:36:02,619
Something like that.

456
00:36:06,277 --> 00:36:10,529
It's a supersonic. The most advanced plane
ever built.

457
00:36:11,828 --> 00:36:14,888
You should see it in real life.
It's incredible.

458
00:36:14,997 --> 00:36:18,853
Hank, these are the special new recruits I
was telling you about.

459
00:36:18,958 --> 00:36:19,940
This is, Hank McCoy,

460
00:36:20,068 --> 00:36:22,037
One of our most talented young researchers.

461
00:36:22,139 --> 00:36:25,727
How wonderful, another mutant.
Already here.

462
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:28,537
- Why didn't you say?
- Say what?

463
00:36:30,315 --> 00:36:31,905
Because you don't know.

464
00:36:32,704 --> 00:36:35,793
I am so, so terribly sorry!

465
00:36:38,491 --> 00:36:39,611
Hank?

466
00:36:39,736 --> 00:36:41,702
You didn't ask, so I didn't tell.

467
00:36:42,232 --> 00:36:45,619
So  your mutation's what?
You're super smart?

468
00:36:45,762 --> 00:36:48,956
I'll say, Hank here graduated honors at the age of fifteen.

469
00:36:49,741 --> 00:36:51,858
I wish that's all it was.

470
00:36:52,044 --> 00:36:55,575
You're among friends now, Hank.
You could show off.

471
00:37:11,637 --> 00:37:12,871
Splendid.

472
00:37:18,596 --> 00:37:20,796
- Sorry.
- Yes, yes.

473
00:37:23,155 --> 00:37:23,647
Wow
[laughing]

474
00:37:26,825 --> 00:37:27,860
tadaa

475
00:37:35,176 --> 00:37:38,328
- You're amazing.
- Really?

476
00:37:43,648 --> 00:37:47,084
<i>(TV): The presence of U.S. missiles in Turkey
represents an unprecedented threat</i>

477
00:37:47,175 --> 00:37:48,860
<i>to the people of the Soviet Union.</i>

478
00:37:48,982 --> 00:37:52,636
<i>Warned Russian Mister Gromeko, earlier today</i>

479
00:37:52,867 --> 00:37:58,112
<i>But he was quick to insist the Russians
would not be the first to initiate any military action.</i>

480
00:37:58,282 --> 00:38:00,559
Yeah, we'll fix that as soon as
we get to Russia.

481
00:38:01,213 --> 00:38:05,359
- Unless the CIA finds us first.
- I'll take care of them too.

482
00:38:06,603 --> 00:38:11,642
If that telepath gets inside your head,
he won't be as much fun as I am.

483
00:38:12,079 --> 00:38:14,031
Already in hand, my love.

484
00:38:23,686 --> 00:38:25,140
The Russians...

485
00:38:27,524 --> 00:38:29,006
...made me this.

486
00:38:32,389 --> 00:38:34,996
So, what am I thinking?

487
00:38:44,448 --> 00:38:45,884
I don't know.

488
00:38:48,647 --> 00:38:52,576
I was thinking that you are the most exquisite
thing that I've ever seen in my life.

489
00:38:56,683 --> 00:38:58,282
And that this needs ice.

490
00:39:00,117 --> 00:39:01,410
Fetch me some.

491
00:39:01,500 --> 00:39:02,885
There's a good girl.

492
00:39:09,435 --> 00:39:09,890
[Beeping of sonar]

493
00:39:28,583 --> 00:39:32,776
I, I promised myself I'd find a cure.
Ever since I was a little boy.

494
00:39:32,874 --> 00:39:36,635
You have no idea what I'd give to feel...

495
00:39:37,180 --> 00:39:38,964
- ...normal.
- Normal.

496
00:39:43,490 --> 00:39:45,785
Charles has never understood.

497
00:39:46,096 --> 00:39:49,432
He's different, but he's never had to hide.

498
00:39:50,167 --> 00:39:54,366
Hank this serum that you're making,
it doesn't affect abilities, right?

499
00:39:54,420 --> 00:39:57,165
Just appearance.
Normalizes it.

500
00:39:57,292 --> 00:39:58,473
Yeah.

501
00:39:59,272 --> 00:40:01,017
Do you think it would work on me?

502
00:40:02,343 --> 00:40:04,694
I can look into it, if you'd like.

503
00:40:04,695 --> 00:40:08,308
That's the least I can do after asking you to
come down here to listen to a weird request.

