01:00:54,949 --> 01:00:57,340
then the way these one stare at me.

757
01:00:58,308 --> 01:00:59,614
At us.

758
01:01:02,386 --> 01:01:02,904
[bump]

759
01:01:02,905 --> 01:01:03,905
[Multiple bumps]

760
01:01:07,609 --> 01:01:08,819
What was that?

761
01:01:11,022 --> 01:01:12,827
I don't know, but something doesn't feel right.

762
01:01:12,828 --> 01:01:13,828
[more bumps]

763
01:01:21,831 --> 01:01:26,153
- No news of Shaw?
- Not a peep, nothing through that back channel.

764
01:01:26,154 --> 01:01:27,154
[loud bump]

765
01:01:27,719 --> 01:01:28,462
[Sharp loud bump]

766
01:01:32,863 --> 01:01:33,544
[snap in]

767
01:01:33,773 --> 01:01:34,006
[Snap out]

768
01:01:39,450 --> 01:01:40,638
What is that?

769
01:01:41,100 --> 01:01:41,639
ahhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh

770
01:01:43,250 --> 01:01:43,674
[boom]
Ahhhhah

771
01:01:47,012 --> 01:01:48,102
- woahhowwwhhh
- ahhhahhhhh

772
01:01:57,840 --> 01:01:59,387
We have an intruder on the main atrium.

773
01:01:59,640 --> 01:02:02,253
- Where are the mutants?
- You take another step, I'm going to put you down.

774
01:02:02,487 --> 01:02:05,003
Of course you will, but where do I find
the more evolved people?

775
01:02:06,782 --> 01:02:07,861
Send back-up now!

776
01:02:11,081 --> 01:02:13,633
Get back, get back, do not leave that room.
We're under attack.

777
01:02:13,944 --> 01:02:15,997
- Look out!
- Shoot , shoot it !

778
01:02:15,998 --> 01:02:16,998
[ rattle of machine-gun fire ]

779
01:02:29,860 --> 01:02:30,880
Where are the mutants?

780
01:02:31,107 --> 01:02:33,130
Put that man down or we will open fire.

781
01:02:43,054 --> 01:02:45,275
[Clash of bazooka]

782
01:02:45,276 --> 01:02:46,276
[crackle of fire]

783
01:02:59,162 --> 01:03:01,449
Stay here my ass.
Let's go!

784
01:03:06,885 --> 01:03:08,714
- Get back!
- We can help, we can help!

785
01:03:11,829 --> 01:03:15,497
[chain reaction like explosion]

786
01:04:09,300 --> 01:04:12,120
Wait, wait, you want the mutants?
They're right through that door.

787
01:04:12,161 --> 01:04:13,573
Just let us normal people go.

788
01:04:13,854 --> 01:04:14,980
We're no threat...
[Smashing of bones]

789
01:04:24,432 --> 01:04:25,370
Where's the telepath?

790
01:04:26,203 --> 01:04:27,905
- Not here.
- Too bad.

791
01:04:28,718 --> 01:04:30,436
Now I can take this silly thing off.

792
01:04:32,959 --> 01:04:35,752
Good evening
My name is, Sebastian Shaw.

793
01:04:38,017 --> 01:04:40,277
And I am not here to hurt you.

794
01:04:40,423 --> 01:04:41,214
Freeze!

795
01:04:42,059 --> 01:04:42,923
Azazel...

796
01:04:47,029 --> 01:04:49,751
My friends, there's a revolution coming.

797
01:04:50,626 --> 01:04:53,895
When mankind discovers who we are,
what we can do.

798
01:04:54,182 --> 01:04:55,785
Each of us will face a choice.

799
01:04:56,666 --> 01:05:01,133
Be enslaved, or rise up to rule.

800
01:05:02,155 --> 01:05:05,301
Choose freely, but know that if you are not with us,

801
01:05:05,301 --> 01:05:08,139
then by definition you are against us.

802
01:05:08,992 --> 01:05:14,977
So, you can stay, and fight for the
people who hate, and fear you.

803
01:05:15,870 --> 01:05:20,022
Or you can join me.
And live like kings.

804
01:05:26,220 --> 01:05:27,553
And Queens.

805
01:05:39,111 --> 01:05:40,786
- Angel?
- Are you kidding me?

806
01:05:41,617 --> 01:05:44,768
Come on, we don't belong here.

807
01:05:45,623 --> 01:05:47,594
And that's nothing to be ashamed of.

808
01:05:52,846 --> 01:05:54,192
We have to do something.

809
01:06:09,993 --> 01:06:12,992
Stop, I'm coming with you.

810
01:06:16,801 --> 01:06:17,902
Good choice.

811
01:06:19,552 --> 01:06:21,638
So tell me about your mutation.

812
01:06:22,377 --> 01:06:23,969
Well, I adapt to survive.

813
01:06:27,503 --> 01:06:30,598
- So I guess I'm coming with you.
- I like that.

814
01:06:37,476 --> 01:06:39,171
- Alex, do it!
- Get out!

815
01:06:39,172 --> 01:06:40,172
Do it.

816
01:06:41,171 --> 01:06:44,084
<Whirling, swirling, and swoosh>

817
01:06:45,421 --> 01:06:46,860
Protecting your fellow mutants?

818
01:06:48,319 --> 01:06:51,298
It's a noble gesture.
Feels good.

819
01:06:57,644 --> 01:06:59,105
Adapt to this.

820
01:07:29,786 --> 01:07:33,047
Moscow, Russia

821
01:07:34,304 --> 01:07:35,495
[sonic boom]

822
01:07:43,408 --> 01:07:44,408
Hello.

823
01:07:46,399 --> 01:07:54,616
Once again, my sympathies for your
treatment at the hands of the CIA.

824
01:07:54,617 --> 01:07:56,895
These American's are ruthless.

825
01:07:57,876 --> 01:08:02,119
Now they have their missiles placed in Turkey.

826
01:08:03,194 --> 01:08:07,766
I expect you'll be planning new
missile sites of your own.

827
01:08:07,767 --> 01:08:14,250
Somewhere where you know the American early
warning system won't help.

828
01:08:14,910 --> 01:08:19,540
I hear Cuba is lovely this time of year.

829
01:08:19,621 --> 01:08:22,388
And so close to Florida.

830
01:08:23,595 --> 01:08:25,034
Missiles in Cuba?

831
01:08:27,789 --> 01:08:29,031
You're serious?

832
01:08:29,698 --> 01:08:32,778
We may as well declare war.

833
01:08:34,162 --> 01:08:36,084
Maybe I wasn't clear enough.

834
01:08:38,588 --> 01:08:40,490
You will make this happen.

835
01:08:43,012 --> 01:08:44,043
Okay.

836
01:08:44,738 --> 01:08:47,216
Let's see what KGB think about this.

837
01:08:51,654 --> 01:08:54,777
Hello, General Armivolkoff.

838
01:08:58,009 --> 01:08:59,798
It's nothing.

839
01:09:16,009 --> 01:09:16,770
Raven.

840
01:09:23,322 --> 01:09:25,265
We've made arrangements for you to
be taken home immediately.

841
01:09:25,545 --> 01:09:26,893
- We're not going home.
- What?

842
01:09:27,446 --> 01:09:30,323
- He's not going back to prison.
- They killed, Darwin.

843
01:09:30,747 --> 01:09:32,358
All the more reason for you to leave.

844
01:09:32,583 --> 01:09:33,487
This is over.

845
01:09:33,966 --> 01:09:37,331
Darwin is dead, Charles.
And we can't even bury him.

846
01:09:40,658 --> 01:09:42,173
We can avenge him.

847
01:09:45,648 --> 01:09:46,998
Erik, word please.

848
01:09:51,027 --> 01:09:53,631
- They're just kids.
- No, they were kids.

849
01:09:54,196 --> 01:09:56,336
Shaw has his army, we need ours.

850
01:10:02,423 --> 01:10:05,583
We'll have to train.
All of us.

851
01:10:06,490 --> 01:10:08,262
- Yes?
- Yeah.

852
01:10:09,161 --> 01:10:10,447
Well we can't stay here.

853
01:10:10,930 --> 01:10:13,348
Even if they reopen the department,
it's not safe.

854
01:10:14,321 --> 01:10:16,314
We've got nowhere to go.

855
01:10:19,080 --> 01:10:20,268
Yes, we do.

856
01:10:21,215 --> 01:10:23,017
The law says we've got to turn her over.

857
01:10:23,282 --> 01:10:25,347
The law applies to human beings.

858
01:10:25,585 --> 01:10:28,642
The same laws don't apply to mutants.
They're too dangerous.

859
01:10:28,961 --> 01:10:32,608
Times like this, security is more
important than liberty.

860
01:10:33,161 --> 01:10:37,812
- There's a war coming, John.
- Yes, but a war with who?

861
01:10:52,013 --> 01:10:53,199
Excellent question.

862
01:10:54,228 --> 01:10:56,043
Though I won't call it a war exactly.

863
01:10:57,074 --> 01:10:59,997
That suggests both sides stand an
equal chance of winning.

864
01:11:10,163 --> 01:11:12,596
Captain, no sign of any American ships.

865
01:11:12,597 --> 01:11:15,200
Maintain course, full ahead.

866
01:11:15,929 --> 01:11:18,414
The Russians have sent their warheads to Cuba.

867
01:11:18,868 --> 01:11:20,947
We have a week before their ship hits the coast.

868
01:11:21,211 --> 01:11:25,332
Our fleet can be on this line,
when the Russian missile ship arrives.

869
01:11:26,030 --> 01:11:30,983
If that ship crosses the line, they will have
declared war against the United States.

870
01:11:32,016 --> 01:11:34,939
We will have no choice but to retaliate
with a full nuclear response.

871
01:11:35,940 --> 01:11:37,190
Do we agree?

872
01:11:42,317 --> 01:11:43,603
Dispatch the Seventh fleet.

873
01:11:46,981 --> 01:11:50,507
- This is yours?
- No, it's ours.

874
01:11:56,974 --> 01:11:59,786
Honestly Charles, I don't know how you survived.

875
01:12:00,303 --> 01:12:01,836
Living in such hardship.

876
01:12:02,138 --> 01:12:04,711
Well it was a hardship softened by me.

877
01:12:08,016 --> 01:12:10,541
Come on, time for the tour.

878
01:12:17,787 --> 01:12:20,346
Moscow, Russia

879
01:12:22,846 --> 01:12:24,561
Dear comrades.

880
01:12:24,562 --> 01:12:32,109
The United States have dispatched
war ships for Cuba.

881
01:12:32,690 --> 01:12:36,600
This leaves us with no choice.

882
01:12:37,937 --> 01:12:41,347
Comrade First Secretary.

883
01:12:42,090 --> 01:12:45,181
We must send in our fleet.

884
01:12:47,912 --> 01:12:49,874
Dispatch the fleet!

885
01:12:49,875 --> 01:12:50,875
[applause]

886
01:12:52,513 --> 01:12:52,666
[Flash]

887
01:12:55,590 --> 01:12:58,422
<i>(TV): President Kennedy has
signed a formal proclamation.</i>

888
01:12:58,624 --> 01:13:02,298
<i>Setting up a blockade of all missiles,
armed for Cuba.</i>

889
01:13:03,374 --> 01:13:09,593
<i>The Soviet Union reacted by terming it
as step along the road to unleashing a thermal nuclear war.</i>

890
01:13:20,248 --> 01:13:22,640
- You're sure?
- I'm sure.

891
01:13:23,666 --> 01:13:24,391
Hold it.

892
01:13:31,732 --> 01:13:33,797
No, I can't I'm sorry.

893
01:13:34,040 --> 01:13:35,193
I can't shoot anybody point blank,

894
01:13:35,422 --> 01:13:36,173
let alone my friend.

895
01:13:36,451 --> 01:13:38,075
Oh come on, you know I can deflect it.

896
01:13:38,318 --> 01:13:39,569
You're always telling me I should push myself.

897
01:13:39,890 --> 01:13:43,026
If you know you can deflect it, then
you're not challenging yourself.

898
01:13:44,755 --> 01:13:47,373
Whatever happened to the man
who was trying to raise a submarine?

899
01:13:48,443 --> 01:13:49,193
What, I can't.

900
01:13:50,384 --> 01:13:52,842
Something that big, I need the situation, the anger.

901
01:13:53,072 --> 01:13:54,446
No, the anger isn't enough.

902
01:13:55,377 --> 01:13:56,970
It's gotten the job done all this time.

903
01:13:57,230 --> 01:13:58,781
It's nearly gotten you killed all this time.

904
01:14:00,315 --> 01:14:01,144
Hey, come here.

905
01:14:02,294 --> 01:14:03,563
Let's try something a little more challenging.

906
01:14:05,860 --> 01:14:08,885
My step-father took the possibility
of nuclear war quite seriously.

907
01:14:09,133 --> 01:14:10,068
This way.

908
01:14:10,208 --> 01:14:12,325
That's why he had this bunker built down here.

909
01:14:12,573 --> 01:14:14,893
I thought we could use it as a practice range of sort.

910
01:14:15,114 --> 01:14:16,232
You don't think I'm going to blow though the walls?

911
01:14:16,867 --> 01:14:19,368
No, he had this place built to
with stand a nuclear bomb.

912
01:14:19,590 --> 01:14:21,041
I think it can handle you, Alex.

913
01:14:21,227 --> 01:14:22,995
You know when I do this,
bad things tend to happen.

914
01:14:24,016 --> 01:14:26,954
It's because you can't control it.
It controls you.

915
01:14:28,029 --> 01:14:30,710
That's why we're here, Alex.
To start your training.

916
01:14:31,336 --> 01:14:31,909
[Howls]

917
01:14:31,910 --> 01:14:32,910
<Glass board shatter>

918
01:14:33,956 --> 01:14:34,942
[Laughs]

919
01:14:35,785 --> 01:14:37,002
What you're doing is incredible.

920
01:14:37,270 --> 01:14:40,057
You're hitting a pitch sound that at
the same resonate frequency of the glass.

921
01:14:40,282 --> 01:14:41,054
That's why it shatters.

922
01:14:41,353 --> 01:14:44,635
This is like any other muscle in the body.
You can control it.

923
01:14:47,110 --> 01:14:49,578
"In each of us, two natures are at war."

924
01:14:50,065 --> 01:14:51,484
Robert Louis Stevenson,
"Jekyll and Hyde".

925
01:14:51,787 --> 01:14:52,529
Top marks.

926
01:14:53,032 --> 01:14:54,891
Still it really wasn't really about good
and evil. Was it, Hank.

927
01:14:55,095 --> 01:14:58,110
It was about man's animal nature,
and his struggle to control it.

928
01:14:58,315 --> 01:14:59,283
To conform.

929
01:14:59,549 --> 01:15:01,581
It is that struggle which is holding you back.

930
01:15:02,254 --> 01:15:04,497
Jekyll is afraid of what he could be capable of.

931
01:15:04,934 --> 01:15:05,920
You are too.

932
01:15:06,639 --> 01:15:08,919
If you're serious about me doing this,
you might want to get back.

933
01:15:09,361 --> 01:15:12,542
- Of course, should I shut the door?
- Yeah.

934
01:15:15,670 --> 01:15:16,544
Whenever you're ready.

935
01:15:24,527 --> 01:15:25,371
My god.

936
01:15:29,145 --> 01:15:31,127
I will teach you to control this, Alex.

937
01:15:34,862 --> 01:15:36,314
You're sure that this will work.

938
01:15:37,024 --> 01:15:39,125
Anything is possible. I based the design...

939
01:15:39,125 --> 01:15:41,452
Hank, stop talking.
Come on.

940
01:15:41,595 --> 01:15:43,331
Now remember, scream as hard as you can.

941
01:15:43,601 --> 01:15:45,254
You need the sound waves to be supersonic.

942
01:15:45,472 --> 01:15:47,211
Catch them at the right angle,
and they should carry you.

943
01:15:47,966 --> 01:15:51,104
"They should carry me."
That's reassuring.

944
01:15:52,000 --> 01:15:52,851
Good luck.

945
01:15:53,606 --> 01:15:54,878
And don't forget to scream.

946
01:16:04,817 --> 01:16:08,027
If you want to beat me this time,
you have to set the beast free.

947
01:16:09,692 --> 01:16:13,385
On your marks, get set...GO!

948
01:16:29,016 --> 01:16:30,207
Oh, congratulations my friend.

949
01:16:30,895 --> 01:16:32,449
Robert Louis Stevenson
would have been proud.

950
01:16:34,683 --> 01:16:35,605
Impressive, Hank.

951
01:16:36,273 --> 01:16:38,042
Feet like those, all you need is a red nose.

952
01:16:38,430 --> 01:16:39,350
Right, Bozo?

953
01:16:40,211 --> 01:16:41,664
- I'm done here.
- Thank you, Alex

954
01:16:43,376 --> 01:16:44,306
Come on, Hank.

955
01:16:55,455 --> 01:16:58,299
If you're using half the concentration to look normal.

956
01:16:58,679 --> 01:17:01,308
Then you're only half paying attention to
whatever else you do.

957
01:17:02,082 --> 01:17:04,199
Just pointing out something that could save your life.

958
01:17:09,027 --> 01:17:10,797
You want society to accept you.

959
01:17:11,779 --> 01:17:13,549
But you can't even accept yourself.

960
01:17:20,356 --> 01:17:21,254
Sexy.

961
01:17:22,528 --> 01:17:23,355
This is just the prototype.

962
01:17:23,556 --> 01:17:25,744
The real will look considerably better
it'll be a whole suit.

963
01:17:26,043 --> 01:17:31,020
See these sensors measure your energy output,
this panel focuses it and the excess is absorbed.

964
01:17:31,124 --> 01:17:33,418
All right try hitting the one in the middle,
just the one in the middle, mind.

965
01:17:34,355 --> 01:17:35,077
Good luck.

966
01:17:45,617 --> 01:17:48,330
You ought to see this. Your genes are
extraordinary, you know that.

967
01:17:48,456 --> 01:17:50,290
Your cells age at half the rate of a normal human.

968
01:17:50,519 --> 01:17:52,479
When you're forty you will still
have the looks of a teenager.

969
01:17:53,180 --> 01:17:56,463
You have the most incredible cellular
structure I've ever seen.

970
01:18:01,952 --> 01:18:03,675
You truly believe I'll fly this time?

971
01:18:03,934 --> 01:18:05,208
Unreservedly.

972
01:18:05,625 --> 01:18:06,842
- I trust you.
- The task.

973
01:18:07,076 --> 01:18:08,436
- I don't trust him.
- Say nothing.

974
01:18:09,997 --> 01:18:10,840
I'm going to die!

975
01:18:12,264 --> 01:18:13,864
All, look we're not going to make you do anything
that your not so...

976
01:18:13,865 --> 01:18:17,732
- Here, let me help him.
- Erik!

977
01:18:21,323 --> 01:18:22,428
[howling continuously]

978
01:18:29,439 --> 01:18:30,439
Whaoooo!

979
01:18:36,977 --> 01:18:38,978
Wahhh hooo!

980
01:18:39,038 --> 01:18:39,765
What?

981
01:18:40,486 --> 01:18:42,052
You know you were thinking the same.

982
01:18:43,148 --> 01:18:46,506
Wonderful work Hank, thank you very much.
All right Alex, I want you to hit the X.

983
01:18:47,274 --> 01:18:49,041
And try not to hit me, there's a good chap.

984
01:18:49,851 --> 01:18:52,495
- You're serious?
- I'm very serious.

985
01:18:52,908 --> 01:18:54,856
I have complete and utter faith in you.

986
01:19:07,986 --> 01:19:11,461
- Am I still a Bozo?
- Yes, Hank. You're still a Bozo.

987
01:19:12,707 --> 01:19:13,781
But nice job.

988
01:19:17,015 --> 01:19:17,952
See that?

989
01:19:18,776 --> 01:19:20,216
Try turning it to face us.

990
01:19:39,844 --> 01:19:45,210
You know, I believe the true focus lies
somewhere between rage and serenity.

991
01:19:46,903 --> 01:19:49,068
Would you mind, if I...?

992
01:20:16,448 --> 01:20:18,109
[shiver]

993
01:20:23,082 --> 01:20:24,538
What did you just do to me?

994
01:20:26,167 --> 01:20:29,465
I accessed the brightest corner
of your memory system.

995
01:20:31,562 --> 01:20:33,784
It's a very beautiful memory Erik, thank you.

996
01:20:34,973 --> 01:20:36,835
I didn't know I still had that.

997
01:20:38,096 --> 01:20:40,147
There's so much more to you than you know.

998
01:20:40,831 --> 01:20:45,897
Not just pain, and anger.
There's good too, I felt it.

999
01:20:46,902 --> 01:20:48,979
And when you can access all that.

1000
01:20:49,323 --> 01:20:51,950
You will possess a power no one can match.

1001
01:20:53,201 --> 01:20:54,546
Not even me.

1002
01:20:56,404 --> 01:20:58,555
So, come on. Try again.

1003
01:21:14,669 --> 01:21:17,206
[dish clanking]

1004
01:21:33,563 --> 01:21:36,530
[beaming]

1005
01:21:39,966 --> 01:21:40,694
- Hey!
-Well done.

1006
01:21:41,260 --> 01:21:43,070
The President is about to make his address.

1007
01:21:45,230 --> 01:21:49,310
<i>It shall be the policy of this nation
to regard any nuclear missile,</i>

1008
01:21:49,470 --> 01:21:52,747
<i>...crossing the embargo line, that surrounds Cuba.</i>

1009
01:21:53,051 --> 01:21:56,801
<i>As an attack by the Soviet Union
on the United States.</i>

1010
01:21:57,299 --> 01:22:01,332
<i>Requiring a full retaliatory response.
Upon the Soviet Union.</i>

1011
01:22:01,332 --> 01:22:03,417
- Thats' where we're going to find, Shaw'
- How do you know?

1012
01:22:03,670 --> 01:22:06,475
Two super powers facing off, and
he wants' to start world war III.

1013
01:22:07,398 --> 01:22:08,835
He won't leave anything to chance.

1014
01:22:09,261 --> 01:22:12,967
So much for diplomacy.
I suggest you all get a good night sleep.

1015
01:22:13,934 --> 01:22:15,379
<i>...ultimately leads to war.</i>

1016
01:22:16,597 --> 01:22:20,465
<i>Tensions mount as the Soviet Missile
ship nears Cuba.</i>

1017
01:22:21,039 --> 01:22:25,349
<i>All diplomatic efforts to avert
Nuclear war have thus far failed.</i>

1018
01:22:25,882 --> 01:22:30,119
<i>As the American people ready themselves,
for the likelihood of an atomic attack.</i>

1019
01:22:30,384 --> 01:22:32,846
<i>There are widespread reports of panic wide.</i>

1020
01:22:33,642 --> 01:22:35,219
<i>Supermarkets cleared.</i>

1021
01:22:35,456 --> 01:22:38,103
<i>As shelters unused since the second world war,</i>

1022
01:22:38,351 --> 01:22:40,521
<i>are stocked for what may lie ahead.</i>

1023
01:22:40,929 --> 01:22:45,033
<i>In all its history, American has never
faced a greater threat.</i>

1024
01:22:45,586 --> 01:22:49,247
The world is primed for war.
And there's no one to stop me.

1025
01:22:55,238 --> 01:22:56,105
Come in.

1026
01:22:56,973 --> 01:22:57,973
Hey.

1027
01:22:59,316 --> 01:23:00,315
Got a surprise for you.

1028
01:23:09,723 --> 01:23:12,651
I isolated the right marker in your DNA sample.

1029
01:23:13,340 --> 01:23:15,041
The serum works like an anti-biotic.

1030
01:23:15,338 --> 01:23:17,890
Attacking the cells that cause our physical mutation.

1031
01:23:18,544 --> 01:23:20,542
It won't affect your abilities,
just your appearance.

1032
01:23:23,944 --> 01:23:25,388
Do you still want to do this?

1033
01:23:27,018 --> 01:23:28,861
Should we have to hide?

1034
01:23:30,424 --> 01:23:31,425
You already do.

1035
01:23:32,400 --> 01:23:34,893
You're hiding right now.
Like I have my whole life.

1036
01:23:36,052 --> 01:23:38,564
I don't want to feel like a freak, all the time.

1037
01:23:38,565 --> 01:23:40,308
- I just want to look...
- ...normal.

1038
01:23:40,715 --> 01:23:41,594
Yeah.

1039
01:23:48,940 --> 01:23:50,378
Hank, don't.

1040
01:23:52,274 --> 01:23:56,379
You're beautiful, Hank.
Everything you are, you're perfect.

1041
01:23:59,193 --> 01:24:02,218
Look at all of us. Look at
all we've achieved this week.

1042
01:24:02,571 --> 01:24:04,216
All we will achieve.

1043
01:24:05,780 --> 01:24:10,701
We are different. But we shouldn't
be trying to fit into society.

1044
01:24:11,848 --> 01:24:14,232
Society should inspire and be more like us.

1045
01:24:15,922 --> 01:24:18,912
Mutant, and proud.

1046
01:24:24,115 --> 01:24:27,839
It behooves me to tell you,
but even if we save the world tomorrow.

1047
01:24:28,043 --> 01:24:30,202
And mutants are accepted into society.

1048
01:24:31,149 --> 01:24:33,860
My feet and your natural blue form.

1049
01:24:34,917 --> 01:24:36,668
Will never be deemed beautiful.

1050
01:24:42,311 --> 01:24:43,692
You look beautiful now.

1051
01:24:45,681 --> 01:24:48,681
We need this cure.

1052
01:25:15,773 --> 01:25:20,728
Cuba, Russia, America makes no difference.

1053
01:25:21,679 --> 01:25:24,308
Shaw's declared war on mankind,
on all of us.

1054
01:25:24,798 --> 01:25:25,913
He has to be stopped.

1055
01:25:26,876 --> 01:25:28,821
I'm going to kill him.

1056
01:25:30,913 --> 01:25:32,645
Do you have it, i need to know that ?

1057
01:25:36,560 --> 01:25:37,252
[chuckle]

1058
01:25:39,211 --> 01:25:41,492
You've known that all along
why I was here, Charles.

1059
01:25:41,961 --> 01:25:43,227
But things have changed.

1060
01:25:44,276 --> 01:25:46,325
What started as a covert mission,

1061
01:25:46,563 --> 01:25:49,559
...tomorrow mankind will know that mutants exist.

1062
01:25:49,562 --> 01:25:51,780
Shaw, us... they won't differentiate.

1063
01:25:52,395 --> 01:25:55,844
They'll fear us, and that
fear will turn to hatred.

1064
01:25:56,300 --> 01:25:59,472
Not if we stop a war.
Not if we can prevent, Shaw.

1065
01:25:59,706 --> 01:26:01,505
Not if we risk our lives doing so.

1066
01:26:01,786 --> 01:26:02,834
Would they do the same for us?

1067
01:26:03,114 --> 01:26:04,600
We have it in us to be the better man.

1068
01:26:04,850 --> 01:26:06,387
We already are.

1069
01:26:06,820 --> 01:26:08,385
We're the next stage of human evolution.

1070
01:26:08,604 --> 01:26:10,104
- You said it yourself.
- No, not.

1071
01:26:10,701 --> 01:26:12,565
Are you really so naive?

1072
01:26:12,566 --> 01:26:15,234
As to think they won't battle their own extinction?

1073
01:26:16,785 --> 01:26:19,095
- Or is it arrogance?
- I'm sorry !?.

1074
01:26:20,343 --> 01:26:22,181
After tomorrow they're going to turn on us.

1075
01:26:22,331 --> 01:26:25,562
And you're blind to it, because you
believe they're all like Moira.

1076
01:26:25,863 --> 01:26:27,675
And you believe they're all like, Shaw.

1077
01:26:30,182 --> 01:26:33,025
Listen to me, very carefully my friend.

1078
01:26:34,308 --> 01:26:37,342
Killing Shaw will not bring you peace.

1079
01:26:39,031 --> 01:26:40,961
Peace was never an option.

1080
01:27:01,136 --> 01:27:03,246
[Squeeze]

1081
01:27:05,647 --> 01:27:06,801
[Sigh]

1082
01:27:16,816 --> 01:27:17,911
[chuckle]

1083
01:27:27,615 --> 01:27:28,597
No.

1084
01:27:30,990 --> 01:27:31,990
No.

1085
01:27:38,198 --> 01:27:41,030
[twang of body expansion]

1086
01:27:50,359 --> 01:27:51,842
[clatter of stuff on desk]

1087
01:28:00,741 --> 01:28:01,773
Well...

1088
01:28:04,179 --> 01:28:05,497
This is a surprise.

1089
01:28:05,998 --> 01:28:07,188
The nice kind?

1090
01:28:09,261 --> 01:28:11,642
Get out Raven, I wanna go to bed.

1091
01:28:12,881 --> 01:28:14,216
Maybe in a few years.

1092
01:28:17,519 --> 01:28:18,538
[Hissing: changing form]

1093
01:28:19,194 --> 01:28:20,304
How about now?

1094
01:28:25,890 --> 01:28:27,432
I prefer the real, Raven.

1095
01:28:29,297 --> 01:28:30,537
[Hissing]

1096
01:28:31,323 --> 01:28:33,841
I said the real, Raven.

1097
01:28:37,873 --> 01:28:39,681
[Hissing]

1098
01:28:43,847 --> 01:28:45,255
Perfection.

1099
01:28:49,591 --> 01:28:52,906
- Could you pass me my robe?
- You don't have to hide.

1100
01:28:57,903 --> 01:29:01,278
Have you ever looked at a tiger,
and thought you ought to cover it up?

1101
01:29:03,798 --> 01:29:05,440
No, but...

1102
01:29:05,726 --> 01:29:07,423
You're an exquisite creature, Raven.

1103
01:29:09,369 --> 01:29:11,607
Only in life the world tries to tame you.

1104
01:29:12,732 --> 01:29:14,091
It's time for you to be free.

1105
01:29:35,097 --> 01:29:37,092
You know sometimes I wonder
what my life would have been like.

1106
01:29:37,092 --> 01:29:39,061
If you hadn't found me here that night.

1107
01:29:39,646 --> 01:29:41,878
Sorry what ?,
You Ed..eah...ah.

1108
01:29:43,323 --> 01:29:44,655
For god's sake, Raven!

1109
01:29:45,248 --> 01:29:47,592
Where are you clothes?
Put some, put some clothes on.

1110
01:29:47,766 --> 01:29:49,536
That's not what you said when you first saw me.

1111
01:29:50,265 --> 01:29:52,825
But I guess pets are always cuter
when they're little, right?

1112
01:29:53,952 --> 01:29:55,480
Raven, I don't know what's got into you lately.

1113
01:29:56,206 --> 01:29:57,347
I thought you'd be in a good mood.

1114
01:29:58,234 --> 01:30:03,080
Hank tells me he's found the
answer to your cosmetic problem.

1115
01:30:05,394 --> 01:30:07,798
You going to tell me what's the matter?
Or will I have to read your mind?

1116
01:30:08,027 --> 01:30:09,646
You promised me you would never do that.

1117
01:30:09,952 --> 01:30:14,352
Until recently, I never had to use my powers
to know what you were thinking, Raven.

1118
01:30:14,503 --> 01:30:18,169
You know Charles, I used to think
it was gonna be you and me against the world.

1119
01:30:18,481 --> 01:30:22,021
And no matter how bad the world gets,
you don't want to be against it, do you?

1120
01:30:22,048 --> 01:30:23,141
You want to be a part of it.

1121
01:30:24,106 --> 01:30:24,775
ahhh

1122
01:30:30,572 --> 01:30:33,528
<i>Gone to the airbase, bring the crate marked X.
Hank</i>

1123
01:30:35,921 --> 01:30:36,648
[squeaking of the door]

1124
01:30:45,559 --> 01:30:46,706
What the hell happened here?

1125
01:30:55,339 --> 01:30:56,603
Hank has been busy.

1126
01:30:57,144 --> 01:30:58,521
Do we really have to wear these?

1127
01:30:59,416 --> 01:31:02,069
As none of us has mutated to enjoy extreme G force,

1128
01:31:02,288 --> 01:31:05,233
or being riddled by bullets, I suggest we suit up.

1129
01:31:30,000 --> 01:31:31,066
Where's Hank?

1130
01:31:33,011 --> 01:31:34,199
I'm here.

1131
01:31:44,050 --> 01:31:44,924
Hank?

1132
01:31:50,897 --> 01:31:55,271
It didn't attack the cells.
It enhanced them.

1133
01:31:57,587 --> 01:31:58,692
It didn't work.

1134
01:31:59,369 --> 01:32:00,925
Yes it did, Hank.

1135
01:32:01,275 --> 01:32:05,059
Don't you see?
This is who you were meant to be.

1136
01:32:06,186 --> 01:32:07,741
This is you.

1137
01:32:09,561 --> 01:32:10,907
No more hiding.

1138
01:32:11,780 --> 01:32:12,835
Never looked better, man.

1139
01:32:13,708 --> 01:32:14,285
Hank!

1140
01:32:14,371 --> 01:32:15,566
[Roars]

1141
01:32:16,001 --> 01:32:18,269
Don't mock me.

1142
01:32:18,629 --> 01:32:20,208
Hank, put him down immediately, please.

1143
01:32:20,348 --> 01:32:21,725
Hank...HANK!

1144
01:32:24,484 --> 01:32:26,040
I wasn't.

1145
01:32:26,337 --> 01:32:28,385
Even I got to admit, you look pretty bad ass.

1146
01:32:28,603 --> 01:32:31,825
I think I got a new name for you, Beast.

1147
01:32:31,826 --> 01:32:32,826
[Grunts]

1148
01:32:34,474 --> 01:32:38,827
- You sure you can fly this thing?
- Of course I can, I designed it.

1149
01:32:41,312 --> 01:32:44,572
Cuba

1150
01:32:50,748 --> 01:32:52,002
Status of the cargo ship?

1151
01:32:52,652 --> 01:32:55,764
Bearing 1-8-0, 12 knots.

1152
01:32:57,989 --> 01:33:00,241
Three minutes to the embargo line, sir.

1153
01:33:01,439 --> 01:33:03,445
God help them if they cross it.

1154
01:33:05,836 --> 01:33:07,367
God help us all.

1155
01:33:07,837 --> 01:33:11,094
- Sound general quarters.
- General quarters, general quarters.

1156
01:33:11,374 --> 01:33:13,829
- All hands man battle stations!
- Yes sir.

1157
01:33:14,125 --> 01:33:15,917
Set condition, zebra.

1158
01:33:16,605 --> 01:33:18,777
General quarters, battle stations.

1159
01:33:28,748 --> 01:33:34,430
Captain, we already have our orders.
Why are you so eager for new ones?

1160
01:33:34,860 --> 01:33:38,625
I've lived through one war, comrade.

1161
01:33:39,750 --> 01:33:42,072
I'd prefer not to start another.

1162
01:33:44,317 --> 01:33:46,530
Battle stations, NOW!

1163
01:33:49,439 --> 01:33:54,179
Gun boss, target cargo ship, bearing 1-8-0.

1164
01:33:56,259 --> 01:33:59,272
Fleet reports all weapons ready.

1165
01:33:59,458 --> 01:34:01,375
There's commands From the Kremlin, sir.

1166
01:34:01,793 --> 01:34:05,813
New orders. As of 1025 hours, the cargo
vessel Aral sea, is hereby ordered to...

1167
01:34:05,814 --> 01:34:09,094
...reverse course and return to port in Odessa.

1168
01:34:09,095 --> 01:34:10,554
Aral Sea, come in.

1169
01:34:11,263 --> 01:34:12,935
Aral Sea, come in.

1170
01:34:13,926 --> 01:34:15,339
They are not responding.

1171
01:34:15,340 --> 01:34:16,912
She's not turning around.

1172
01:34:16,913 --> 01:34:19,541
Aral Sea, you are ordered to turn around.

1173
01:34:19,542 --> 01:34:21,254
Do not cross the line.

1174
01:34:22,210 --> 01:34:23,746
Target ready to be fired upon, sir.

1175
01:34:24,137 --> 01:34:26,131
- Stand by to fire.
- Standing by, sir.

1176
01:34:39,655 --> 01:34:41,404
Looks pretty messy out there.

1177
01:34:52,551 --> 01:34:55,207
Aral Sea, you are ordered to turn around.

1178
01:34:56,040 --> 01:34:58,796
The crew of the Aral Sea are all dead.
Shaw's been there.

1179
01:34:58,797 --> 01:35:00,567
He's still here, somewhere.

1180
01:35:00,568 --> 01:35:02,119
He's set the ship on course for the embargo line.

1181
01:35:02,338 --> 01:35:04,657
That ship crosses the line, our
boys are going to blow it up.

1182
01:35:05,073 --> 01:35:06,477
And the war begins.

1183
01:35:07,122 --> 01:35:09,207
Unless they're not on board.

1184
01:35:11,726 --> 01:35:13,875
<i>USS Independence,
this is, Alexander Nevski.</i>

1185
01:35:14,289 --> 01:35:16,520
<i>We have lost control of our cargo ship.</i>

1186
01:35:16,521 --> 01:35:19,309
<i>She's been instructed to stop.
Do not fire.</i>

1187
01:35:19,310 --> 01:35:21,134
<i>Repeat, do not fire.</i>

1188
01:35:21,144 --> 01:35:22,958
They've signaled their
cargo ship to turn around, sir.

1189
01:35:24,450 --> 01:35:25,431
It's a ruse.

1190
01:35:25,761 --> 01:35:28,135
 pay no attention, Stand by to fire.

1191
01:35:29,890 --> 01:35:30,717
- Standing by to fire, sir.
- On my count.

1192
01:35:31,267 --> 01:35:33,047
Five...four...

1193
01:35:56,083 --> 01:35:56,585
ahhhh

1194
01:35:56,620 --> 01:35:57,686
Hold on! Hold on!

1195
01:36:00,906 --> 01:36:01,617
[yowling]

1196
01:36:07,034 --> 01:36:07,858
No!

1197
01:36:08,856 --> 01:36:12,037
[Bang]

1198
01:36:12,557 --> 01:36:16,195
- What was that?
- The Russians, they have fired on their own ship.

1199
01:36:16,746 --> 01:36:18,767
A little warning next time, professor.

1200
01:36:18,860 --> 01:36:19,659
Sorry about that.

1201
01:36:19,877 --> 01:36:21,454
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1202
01:36:22,226 --> 01:36:23,990
Son of a...

1203
01:36:23,990 --> 01:36:26,304
Give me Sinclair on the horn, I want a new set of orders.

1204
01:36:30,218 --> 01:36:32,842
Congratulations, comrade.

1205
01:36:33,038 --> 01:36:36,812
You just averted a Nuclear war.

1206
01:36:37,155 --> 01:36:38,637
What?

1207
01:36:38,638 --> 01:36:40,249
Arrest him, and put him in the cell.

1208
01:36:40,250 --> 01:36:42,234
What? Why?
 What just happened?

1209
01:36:44,154 --> 01:36:45,906
They say the comrade lost his mind.

1210
01:36:46,256 --> 01:36:47,594
The Americans are plotting.

1211
01:36:49,959 --> 01:36:50,845
They're here.

1212
01:36:51,116 --> 01:36:52,908
That telepath is powerful.

1213
01:36:55,555 --> 01:36:57,098
We're moving to a back-up plan.

1214
01:37:00,086 --> 01:37:02,353
- That was inspired, Charles.
- Thank you very much.

1215
01:37:02,557 --> 01:37:03,789
But I still can't locate Shaw.

1216
01:37:04,040 --> 01:37:06,005
He's down there, we need to find him now.

1217
01:37:06,230 --> 01:37:07,101
Hank?

1218
01:37:07,120 --> 01:37:11,426
- Is there anything unusual on the radar scanners?
- No, nothing.

1219
01:37:12,139 --> 01:37:15,717
Well then he must be under water.
And obviously we don't have Sonar.

1220
01:37:17,895 --> 01:37:18,711
Yes we do !.

1221
01:37:19,773 --> 01:37:20,677
Yes we do.

1222
01:37:25,336 --> 01:37:26,556
They were ready for war.

1223
01:37:26,805 --> 01:37:29,356
We just need to strike another match
to light the fuse.

1224
01:37:29,613 --> 01:37:32,371
And we still have the most powerful weapon of all.

1225
01:37:33,113 --> 01:37:34,092
Me.

1226
01:37:34,537 --> 01:37:37,324
Turn the nuclear reactor to 100% output..

1227
01:37:37,324 --> 01:37:40,867
and make sure I'm not disturbed.

1228
01:37:42,984 --> 01:37:45,088
Hank, level the bloody plane!

1229
01:37:50,518 --> 01:37:52,594
Whoa, you back right off.

1230
01:37:53,530 --> 01:37:55,471
Beast, open the Bombay doors.

1231
01:38:03,708 --> 01:38:08,009
Remember, this is a muscle.
You control it.

1232
01:38:08,289 --> 01:38:12,326
You'll be in here the entire time.
We'll see you soon.

1233
01:38:12,660 --> 01:38:18,806
- On my mark. 3, 2, 1 GO!
- WHOA!!!

1234
01:38:34,725 --> 01:38:37,013
Alert the fleet, they may want to take their cams off.

1235
01:38:38,632 --> 01:38:39,373
[Howling]

1236
01:38:43,753 --> 01:38:44,235
amhh

1237
01:38:50,299 --> 01:38:52,048
Banshee is got a location on Shaw.

1238
01:38:54,803 --> 01:38:55,715
You ready for this?

1239
01:38:56,448 --> 01:38:57,615
Let's find out.

1240
01:39:20,386 --> 01:39:21,280
[Hissing]

1241
01:39:44,468 --> 01:39:45,892
[Plane hovering]

1242
01:40:01,443 --> 01:40:05,756
<i>Remember, the point between rage and serenity.</i>

1243
01:41:36,170 --> 01:41:38,405
[swirl of vortex]

1244
01:41:32,764 --> 01:41:35,329
Hold on guys, it's going to get bumpy.

1245
01:41:50,854 --> 01:41:52,338
Erik, take my hand!

1246
01:41:54,252 --> 01:42:02,564
[clanging, clanking, scrunching, crashing]

1247
01:42:05,576 --> 01:42:06,262
<Plane wing disjointed>

1248
01:42:06,263 --> 01:42:07,263
[Emergency beeps]

1249
01:42:15,487 --> 01:42:16,636
[crashing]

1250
01:42:19,428 --> 01:42:20,701
[All Screaming]

1251
01:42:26,549 --> 01:42:27,549
Down.

1252
01:42:43,408 --> 01:42:46,311
- Moira, Moira, are you all right?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

1253
01:42:51,174 --> 01:42:52,845
I read the teleporter's mind.

1254
01:42:53,081 --> 01:42:54,974
Shaw's drawing all of the power out of his sub.

1255
01:42:55,236 --> 01:42:57,208
He's turning himself into some kind of nuclear bomb.

1256
01:42:57,397 --> 01:42:59,452
We've got no time, the Geiger
counter's going out of control.

1257
01:42:59,647 --> 01:43:00,669
All right Moira, this is what we're going to do.

1258
01:43:00,928 --> 01:43:03,100
Get on the radio and send both fleet's out immediately.

1259
01:43:03,344 --> 01:43:04,093
I'm going in.

1260
01:43:04,349 --> 01:43:05,719
Beast, Havoc, back him up.

1261
01:43:05,956 --> 01:43:07,819
Erik, I can guide you through once you're in.

1262
01:43:08,050 --> 01:43:10,394
But I need you to shut down
whatever it is that's blocking me.

1263
01:43:10,675 --> 01:43:12,521
Then we just hope to god it's
not too late for me to stop him.

1264
01:43:12,770 --> 01:43:13,742
- Got it.
- Good luck!

1265
01:43:14,523 --> 01:43:16,409
- Raven, stop!
- I'm going out there.

1266
01:43:16,638 --> 01:43:17,414
We don't have time for this.

1267
01:43:17,693 --> 01:43:19,959
Anything comes in that entrance,
Sure you're taking care of it, yes?

1268
01:43:20,884 --> 01:43:21,601
Fine.

1269
01:43:38,126 --> 01:43:39,160
Beast!

1270
01:43:42,941 --> 01:43:44,785
If we go, you go

1271
01:43:47,998 --> 01:43:50,262
We believe Shaw is trying to
detonate some kind of bomb.

1272
01:43:55,511 --> 01:43:57,502
Erik, make for the middle of the vessel.

1273
01:43:57,981 --> 01:43:59,638
That's the point my mind can't penetrate.

1274
01:43:59,639 --> 01:44:01,846
We have to assume that, that's where Shaw is.

1275
01:44:19,831 --> 01:44:22,745
That's the nuclear reactor.
Disable it.

1276
01:44:34,869 --> 01:44:36,632
Stop, don't move.

1277
01:44:41,317 --> 01:44:43,334
[Flaps]

1278
01:44:44,501 --> 01:44:45,534
Get down!

1279
01:44:45,534 --> 01:44:47,059
[spitting fire balls]

1280
01:44:55,433 --> 01:44:57,059
[Continuous howls]

1281
01:45:09,295 --> 01:45:10,827
<i>Erik you're there, you've reached the void.</i>

1282
01:45:11,139 --> 01:45:12,789
He's not here Charles,
Shaw is not here.

1283
01:45:12,871 --> 01:45:15,065
- He's left the sub.
- What? He's got to be there.

1284
01:45:15,286 --> 01:45:17,603
He has to be, there's no where
else he can be, keep looking.

1285
01:45:17,627 --> 01:45:20,197
And I'm telling you he's not,
there's no one here, god damn it!

1286
01:45:23,901 --> 01:45:27,682
Erik, what a pleasant surprise.

1287
01:45:27,925 --> 01:45:29,566
Erik?
Erik!

1288
01:45:32,317 --> 01:45:33,690
So good to see you again.

1289
01:45:38,093 --> 01:45:39,469
[multiple fiery spits]

1290
01:45:50,626 --> 01:45:52,234
May I ask you something?

1291
01:45:53,846 --> 01:45:55,363
Why are you on their side?

1292
01:45:55,747 --> 01:45:56,590
- He's gone.
- What?

1293
01:45:56,816 --> 01:45:59,750
He's gone into the void. I can't
communicate with him there.

1294
01:46:00,044 --> 01:46:02,685
Why fight for a doomed race
who will hunt us down,

1295
01:46:02,686 --> 01:46:05,424
...as soon as they realize
their reign is coming to an end.

1296
01:46:17,321 --> 01:46:19,416
[Howling on soldiers]

1297
01:46:34,115 --> 01:46:35,450
Yeah!

1298
01:46:49,191 --> 01:46:51,274
I'm sorry for what happened in the camps.

1299
01:46:53,383 --> 01:46:54,833
I truly am.

1300
01:47:03,544 --> 01:47:04,534
He's back.

1301
01:47:04,918 --> 01:47:08,065
<i>Erik, whatever you're doing keep
doing it, it's starting to work.</i>

1302
01:47:09,141 --> 01:47:12,390
But everything I did,
I did for you.

1303
01:47:12,494 --> 01:47:13,717
To unlock your power.

1304
01:47:13,717 --> 01:47:17,761
 To make you embrace it.

1305
01:47:19,920 --> 01:47:21,143
<i>It's working.</i>

1306
01:47:21,144 --> 01:47:23,535
I'm starting to see him, but I
can't yet touch his mind.

1307
01:47:27,566 --> 01:47:28,706
[Flaps]

1308
01:47:29,510 --> 01:47:29,966
[Speedy whirl]

1309
01:47:37,802 --> 01:47:40,374
You've come a long way from bending gates.

1310
01:47:40,907 --> 01:47:42,200
I'm so proud of you.

1311
01:47:50,460 --> 01:47:53,103
And you're just starting to scratch the surface.

1312
01:47:53,328 --> 01:47:57,650
Think how much further we could go, together.

1313
01:48:17,093 --> 01:48:19,342
Stop, Azazel!

1314
01:48:24,851 --> 01:48:25,625
[snap]

1315
01:48:29,760 --> 01:48:31,238
[Hissing]

1316
01:48:34,291 --> 01:48:37,139
I don't want to hurt you, Erik.
I never did.

1317
01:48:37,721 --> 01:48:38,904
I want to help you.

1318
01:48:39,138 --> 01:48:42,479
This is our time.
Our age.

1319
01:48:43,423 --> 01:48:46,726
We are the future of the human race.

1320
01:48:47,819 --> 01:48:52,176
You and me, son.
This world could be ours.

1321
01:48:54,493 --> 01:48:57,586
Everything you did, made me stronger.

1322
01:48:59,368 --> 01:49:01,339
Made me the weapon I am today.

1323
01:49:03,605 --> 01:49:04,812
That's the truth.

1324
01:49:06,458 --> 01:49:08,045
I've known it all along.

1325
01:49:14,550 --> 01:49:16,052
You are my creator.

1326
01:49:17,332 --> 01:49:18,199
NOW, Charles!

1327
01:49:20,430 --> 01:49:21,163
Are you okay?

1328
01:49:21,398 --> 01:49:24,130
Moira be quiet, I can only
control this man for so long.

1329
01:49:37,620 --> 01:49:38,875
Sorry, Charles.

1330
01:49:38,876 --> 01:49:41,396
<i>Erik please, be the better man.
You have it in...</i>

1331
01:49:41,396 --> 01:49:42,486
But I dont trust you.

1332
01:49:42,487 --> 01:49:43,984
<i>Erik, there will be no telling what...</i>

1333
01:49:45,661 --> 01:49:46,661
No.

1334
01:49:47,595 --> 01:49:49,518
- Charles?
- Don't do this, Erik!

1335
01:49:56,733 --> 01:50:01,182
If you're in there, I'd like you to know
that I agree with every word you've said.

1336
01:50:03,935 --> 01:50:05,175
We are the future.

1337
01:50:08,221 --> 01:50:09,567
But...

1338
01:50:11,027 --> 01:50:14,480
...unfortunately, you killed my mother.

1339
01:50:23,752 --> 01:50:25,169
This is what we're going to do.

1340
01:50:25,528 --> 01:50:27,484
No, please Erik, no.

1341
01:50:27,827 --> 01:50:31,438
I'm going to count to three.
And I'm going to move the coin.

1342
01:50:33,485 --> 01:50:34,696
One...

1343
01:50:36,456 --> 01:50:38,059
Please, Erik.

1344
01:50:46,180 --> 01:50:47,374
Two...

1345
01:50:54,271 --> 01:50:55,381
Three.

1346
01:50:57,230 --> 01:50:59,170
Aaaaaaaah!

1347
01:51:17,717 --> 01:51:18,832
[ringing of falling coin]

1348
01:51:24,441 --> 01:51:27,272
The Russians share our concerns.

1349
01:51:27,524 --> 01:51:30,197
And will join a strike on all the mutants.

1350
01:51:30,477 --> 01:51:32,513
We can end this threat for good.

1351
01:51:32,741 --> 01:51:34,614
We'll never have another opportunity like this.

1352
01:51:34,681 --> 01:51:36,321
We have an agent on that beach.

1353
01:51:36,620 --> 01:51:39,739
- One agent.
- She's a good agent.

1354
01:51:39,994 --> 01:51:41,436
She's collateral damage.

1355
01:51:47,843 --> 01:51:49,993
Today our fighting stops.

1356
01:51:59,025 --> 01:51:59,811
[Smash of bones]

1357
01:52:14,199 --> 01:52:17,050
Take off your blinders, brothers and sisters.

1358
01:52:17,420 --> 01:52:19,145
The real enemy is out there.

1359
01:52:21,145 --> 01:52:23,345
I feel their guns moving in the water.

1360
01:52:23,660 --> 01:52:25,847
Their metal targeting us.

1361
01:52:26,177 --> 01:52:30,193
Americans, Soviets, humans.

1362
01:52:31,118 --> 01:52:33,197
United in their fear of the unknown.

1363
01:52:34,625 --> 01:52:37,876
A Neanderthal is running scared,
my fellow mutants.

1364
01:52:40,670 --> 01:52:41,940
Go ahead, Charles.

1365
01:52:44,209 --> 01:52:45,686
Tell me I'm wrong.

1366
01:53:05,841 --> 01:53:08,624
Fleet commander this is X-ray Bravo-70.

1367
01:53:08,846 --> 01:53:10,086
Respond, over.

1368
01:53:11,314 --> 01:53:13,885
The beach is secure, call off the attack.

1369
01:53:13,972 --> 01:53:16,394
The beach is targeted and ready to
be fired upon, sir.

1370
01:53:16,585 --> 01:53:18,493
- Stand by.
- Standing by, sir.

1371
01:53:19,971 --> 01:53:20,841
All weapons set.

1372
01:53:22,813 --> 01:53:27,187
Hello?
Hello!

1373
01:53:35,167 --> 01:53:37,411
Fire.
Fire.

1374
01:53:37,412 --> 01:53:40,426
[All sorts of projectiles and rockets launched]
[Boom] / [bang]

1375
01:54:26,223 --> 01:54:28,210
Erik, you said yourself, we're the better men.

1376
01:54:29,071 --> 01:54:30,446
This is the time to prove it.

1377
01:54:34,500 --> 01:54:36,569
There are thousands of men on those ships.

1378
01:54:36,570 --> 01:54:38,367
Good, Honest men.

1379
01:54:38,952 --> 01:54:40,702
They're just following orders.

1380
01:54:42,883 --> 01:54:45,333
I've been at the mercy of men
just following orders.

1381
01:54:50,006 --> 01:54:51,598
Never again.

1382
01:54:55,977 --> 01:54:57,150
Erik, release them.

1383
01:55:08,857 --> 01:55:11,083
I don't want to hurt you,
don't make me.

1384
01:55:12,175 --> 01:55:13,468
Stay back!

1385
01:55:16,177 --> 01:55:17,370
Charles, enough.

1386
01:55:22,320 --> 01:55:23,457
Erik, stop!

1387
01:55:33,777 --> 01:55:36,185
Gentlemen, it's been an honor serving with you.

1388
01:55:36,647 --> 01:55:39,058
Comrades, ......

1389
01:55:46,379 --> 01:55:48,497
[Gunshot]

1390
01:55:52,410 --> 01:55:53,987
[Screaming]

1391
01:56:26,075 --> 01:56:27,167
I'm so sorry.

1392
01:56:27,418 --> 01:56:28,891
I said back off!

1393
01:56:31,063 --> 01:56:33,502
You, you did this!

1394
01:56:37,662 --> 01:56:39,731
Please...

1395
01:56:42,255 --> 01:56:46,024
She didn't do this, Erik.
You did.

1396
01:56:51,171 --> 01:56:52,134
[Gasping for air]

1397
01:56:53,783 --> 01:56:57,440
Us turning on each other,
it's what they want.

1398
01:56:57,843 --> 01:56:59,670
I tried to warn you, Charles.

1399
01:57:02,413 --> 01:57:06,567
I want you by my side.
We're brothers, you and I.

1400
01:57:07,332 --> 01:57:10,260
All of us, together. Protecting each other.

1401
01:57:12,418 --> 01:57:14,245
We want the same thing.

1402
01:57:15,625 --> 01:57:17,041
Oh, my friend.

1403
01:57:17,761 --> 01:57:21,011
I'm sorry, but we do not.

1404
01:57:37,307 --> 01:57:41,333
Charles, I'm sorry, I'm so sorry, Charles.

1405
01:57:41,573 --> 01:57:44,125
It's all right, it's all right.

1406
01:57:47,234 --> 01:57:49,298
His society won't accept us.

1407
01:57:50,630 --> 01:57:52,237
We form our own.

1408
01:57:52,647 --> 01:57:54,711
The humans has played their hand.

1409
01:57:56,988 --> 01:57:59,328
Now we get ready to play ours.

1410
01:58:02,118 --> 01:58:03,479
Who's with me?

1411
01:58:14,891 --> 01:58:16,507
No more hiding.

1412
01:58:42,739 --> 01:58:47,269
You, you should go with him.
It's what you want.

1413
01:58:48,021 --> 01:58:50,213
You promised me you would never read my mind.

1414
01:58:50,761 --> 01:58:51,715
I know.

1415
01:58:52,322 --> 01:58:54,932
I promised you a great many things,
I'm afraid.

1416
01:58:55,715 --> 01:58:56,739
I'm sorry.

1417
01:59:02,224 --> 01:59:03,282
Take care of him.

1418
01:59:19,019 --> 01:59:21,586
And Beast, never forget.

1419
01:59:22,784 --> 01:59:25,740
Mutant and proud.

1420
01:59:34,455 --> 01:59:35,824
Help me out, help him.

1421
01:59:36,908 --> 01:59:38,416
I'm going to get you to a hospital.

1422
01:59:38,417 --> 01:59:41,752
- Wait, don't, Charles, don't move, okay.

1423
01:59:41,753 --> 01:59:47,280
All right, actually I ca.....I...I...

1424
01:59:49,231 --> 01:59:50,600
I can't feel my legs

1425
01:59:52,697 --> 01:59:54,323
I can't feel my legs.

1426
01:59:56,376 --> 01:59:58,043
I can't feel my legs.

1427
02:00:09,940 --> 02:00:13,548
<i>In this week of thanksgiving.
There is much for which we can be grateful.</i>

1428
02:00:13,754 --> 02:00:17,059
<i>As you look back to where we stood,
only four weeks ago.</i>

1429
02:00:17,350 --> 02:00:20,454
<i>The unity of this hemisphere,
the support of our allies.</i>

1430
02:00:20,625 --> 02:00:23,142
<i>And the calm determination of the American people.</i>

1431
02:00:23,633 --> 02:00:26,309
<i>These qualities may be tested many more times.</i>

1432
02:00:26,543 --> 02:00:27,794
<i>In this decade.</i>

1433
02:00:30,937 --> 02:00:33,112
So how many students do you think 
you'll have here?

1434
02:00:33,112 --> 02:00:35,572
Once you get the academy up and running.

1435
02:00:35,844 --> 02:00:39,695
As many as I can manage, and Possibly more.

1436
02:00:42,709 --> 02:00:47,287
You know, one day the government is going
to realize how lucky they were,

1437
02:00:47,491 --> 02:00:49,187
..to have Professor X on their side.

1438
02:00:50,808 --> 02:00:53,073
As I suppose I am on the
road to a professor now, aren't I ?.

1439
02:00:53,302 --> 02:00:54,996
First thing I'll be going bald.

1440
02:00:56,490 --> 02:00:58,606
We're still on the government side, Moira.

1441
02:00:59,347 --> 02:01:01,736
We're still a G-man, just without the G.

1442
02:01:02,409 --> 02:01:04,955
No, you're your own team now.

1443
02:01:05,941 --> 02:01:07,069
It's better.

1444
02:01:08,193 --> 02:01:10,632
You're, "X-Men".

1445
02:01:10,633 --> 02:01:11,633
[chuckle]

1446
02:01:13,214 --> 02:01:14,347
Guess, I'll like the sound of that.

1447
02:01:15,145 --> 02:01:20,979
Moira, for us anonymity will be the first line of defense.

1448
02:01:21,499 --> 02:01:22,937
I know.

1449
02:01:24,129 --> 02:01:27,590
They can threaten me all they want, Charles.

1450
02:01:28,726 --> 02:01:30,699
I'll never tell them where you are.

1451
02:01:31,634 --> 02:01:32,637
Ever.

1452
02:01:33,683 --> 02:01:35,022
I know you won't.

1453
02:01:36,926 --> 02:01:38,392
My love.

1454
02:01:45,844 --> 02:01:48,034
I remember the attack on HQ.

1455
02:01:48,696 --> 02:01:50,243
Leaving to go somewhere else.

1456
02:01:51,215 --> 02:01:54,183
And then this morning, I woke up at home.

1457
02:01:55,094 --> 02:01:56,085
That's it.

1458
02:01:57,486 --> 02:01:59,525
All that time wiped clean from your mind.

1459
02:01:59,962 --> 02:02:01,122
Just gone.

1460
02:02:01,577 --> 02:02:03,373
He can do that.
You don't remember anything?

1461
02:02:04,123 --> 02:02:11,616
Sometimes I get fragments.
Like trees, sunlight.

1462
02:02:14,019 --> 02:02:16,334
- A kiss.
- Aw, Jesus.

1463
02:02:17,212 --> 02:02:20,873
Gentlemen, this is why the CIA
is no place for a woman.

1464
02:02:21,788 --> 02:02:22,801
[Powerful plonk, Crash]

1465
02:02:25,626 --> 02:02:26,636
What the hell was that?

1466
02:02:36,343 --> 02:02:38,411
[scrunching and snapping the door  ]

1467
02:02:43,671 --> 02:02:45,992
I know we've had our differences.

1468
02:02:48,565 --> 02:02:52,120
- Where's your telepath friend?
- Gone.

1469
02:02:53,463 --> 02:02:56,471
Left a bit of a gap in my life.
If I'm to be honest.

1470
02:02:56,601 --> 02:02:58,689
I was rather hoping you would fill it.

1471
02:03:03,857 --> 02:03:04,730
Join us.

1472
02:03:12,331 --> 02:03:13,892
Erik, I believe.

1473
02:03:17,595 --> 02:03:19,311
I prefer...

1474
02:03:21,300 --> 02:03:22,201
...Magneto.

